					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Pregnancy Discrimination</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-07-15T20:53:06+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">July 15, 2014 4:53 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">July 15, 2014 4:53 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/07/15/today-in-small-business-pregnancy-discrimination/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Pregnancy Discrimination" data-description="Understanding the economics of lobsters. The value of the right domain name. And how to get customers to write online reviews.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Nonresidential <a title="Reed Construction Data article." href="//www.reedconstructiondata.com/Market-Intelligence/Articles/2014/7/Non-residential-Construction-Starts-Surged-in-June-1000293W/">construction starts</a> surged in June, and <a title="Wall Street Journal article." href="//online.wsj.com/articles/u-s-retail-sales-rise-modestly-in-june-1405427766">retail sales</a> rose modestly.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here&#8217;s how to explain &#8220;<a title="Globe and Mail (of Toronto) article." href="//www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/my-travels-with-larry/article19557387/">the voodoo of lobster economics</a>.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Americans are <a title="Washington Post article." href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/07/14/americans-are-spending-more-money-this-summer-but-not-on-fun-stuff/">spending more money</a> this summer, according to Gallup, but not on the fun stuff.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some economists are <a title="Washington Times article." href="//www.washingtontimes.com/news/2014/jul/13/economists-see-signs-of-another-market-bubble/">seeing signs</a> of another market bubble (and David Stockman says <a title="Economic Policy Journal article." href="//www.economicpolicyjournal.com/2014/07/the-implosion-is-near-signs-of-bubbles.html">âthe implosionâ</a> is near).</p>
